The defence minister has said that soldiers demanding salary increases and bonuses had orchestrated the seizure. ABIDJAN Soldiers demanding salary increases and the payment of bonuses were behind the seizure of Ivory Coast's second-largest city of Bouake on Friday, the West African nation s defence minister said. It is asked that all soldiers remain calm and return to barracks so that lasting solutions can be found, a statement from Alain-Richard Donwahi read on state-owned television said.